00:55:09.148 --> 00:55:10.440
What are you doing?

778
00:55:10.525 --> 00:55:14.070
<i>Be and be better.
for they existed.</i>

779
00:55:16.197 --> 00:55:17.489
Do you think
that's true?

780
00:55:18.907 --> 00:55:21.119
<i>Hello?</i>

781
00:55:40.346 --> 00:55:41.556
Hey. what can I get for you?

782
00:55:41.639 --> 00:55:43.141
Hey. do you know her?

783
00:55:43.806 --> 00:55:45.518
Uh. no. I don't.

784
00:55:45.601 --> 00:55:47.353
Could you ask someone else?
I think she used to work here.

785
00:55:47.436 --> 00:55:48.853
I'm sorry. there's a line.

786
00:55:48.938 --> 00:55:50.648
I'm gonna need you
to order something.

787
00:55:50.731 --> 00:55:52.817
Oh. I'll have
a double espresso.

788
00:55:52.900 --> 00:55:54.568
And if I can speak to the
manager. that would be great.

789
00:55:54.652 --> 00:55:56.277
Double espresso. is that it?

790
00:55:56.362 --> 00:55:57.447
Yes. And the manager.

791
00:56:03.244 --> 00:56:04.829
Sorry. I can't help you.

792
00:56:05.454 --> 00:56:06.496
But she worked here.

793
00:56:06.581 --> 00:56:08.083
She doesn't work here anymore.

794
00:56:09.875 --> 00:56:11.085
But could you
tell me her name?

795
00:56:11.835 --> 00:56:13.128
Why do you want to find her?

796
00:56:15.715 --> 00:56:17.050
She knew my son.

797
00:56:17.925 --> 00:56:21.221
And he's not doing so well
right now. Health-wise.

798
00:56:22.137 --> 00:56:23.556
And I thought
she'd want to know.

799
00:56:24.389 --> 00:56:25.806
But you've never met her.

800
00:56:26.226 --> 00:56:27.226
No.

801
00:56:27.768 --> 00:56:29.311
And you don't know her name.

802
00:56:30.646 --> 00:56:31.646
No.

803
00:56:32.856 --> 00:56:35.985
Yeah. Then I don't either.

804
00:56:37.070 --> 00:56:38.070
Sorry.

805
00:56:48.581 --> 00:56:49.873
- Hey.
- Hey. George.

806
00:56:49.958 --> 00:56:50.958
What do you need?

807
00:56:51.041 --> 00:56:54.378
I was wondering if you'd ever
seen her around the house.

808
00:56:57.840 --> 00:56:59.509
I... Who is she?

809
00:56:59.592 --> 00:57:01.594
I don't know.
but Yang knew her.

810
00:57:02.052 --> 00:57:03.387
Really? Huh.

811
00:57:04.054 --> 00:57:06.681
I... I didn't know
that bots. uh...

812
00:57:08.143 --> 00:57:11.436
That techno beings could
make friends on their own.

813
00:57:12.896 --> 00:57:14.731
- They were just...
- I... I don't know anything.

814
00:57:14.815 --> 00:57:16.858
I just want to find her.

815
00:57:16.942 --> 00:57:18.027
Hmm.

816
00:57:18.110 --> 00:57:19.820
Let me ask the girls.
Maybe they know something.

817
00:57:19.902 --> 00:57:21.197
Please. Thank you.

818
00:57:21.530 --> 00:57:23.657
Ladies. I need to see you.

819
00:57:24.992 --> 00:57:26.036
What is it?

820
00:57:26.786 --> 00:57:29.496
Just get over here.
And bring the twins.

821
00:57:31.331 --> 00:57:34.168
Vicky just made
the all-star softball team.

822
00:57:34.251 --> 00:57:36.753
You gotta come watch.
I mean. she's just great.

823
00:57:36.835 --> 00:57:37.963
Nice.

824
00:57:40.215 --> 00:57:41.217
What is it?

825
00:57:42.635 --> 00:57:46.181
Mr. Fleming wants to know
if you've seen her around.

826
00:57:48.181 --> 00:57:49.309
Are you sure?

827
00:57:50.768 --> 00:57:52.061
Can we go?

828
00:57:52.561 --> 00:57:54.230
Yeah. Go ahead.

829
00:57:57.025 --> 00:57:58.025
How about you?

830
00:57:59.985 --> 00:58:01.070
Is she in trouble?

831
00:58:02.405 --> 00:58:04.907
- I don't...
- No. No. not at all.

832
00:58:05.364 --> 00:58:06.367
How's Yang?

833
00:58:07.284 --> 00:58:08.536
He's not so good.

834
00:58:09.454 --> 00:58:13.123
You know. I think finding her.
it might help.

835
00:58:14.666 --> 00:58:16.043
Yeah. I've seen her.

836
00:58:16.126 --> 00:58:17.128
You have?

837
00:58:17.503 --> 00:58:19.505
A couple times. At your place.

838
00:58:20.380 --> 00:58:21.547
Did you ever talk to her?

839
00:58:22.300 --> 00:58:25.094
Once. Yang asked me
not to say anything.

840
00:58:25.177 --> 00:58:26.179
Why?

841
00:58:26.721 --> 00:58:28.181
You don't like clones. right?

842
00:58:29.139 --> 00:58:31.891
- No. no. it's not...
- Come on. Vic. No fastballs.

843
00:58:31.976 --> 00:58:33.353
I just...
I've never had the...

844
00:58:33.436 --> 00:58:35.146
- It's... It's fine.
- No. it's not.

845
00:58:35.813 --> 00:58:36.813
Vicky.

846
00:58:36.896 --> 00:58:37.983
She's a clone.

847
00:58:38.733 --> 00:58:39.733
She is?

848
00:58:40.193 --> 00:58:44.530
Yeah. but she's really cool
and nice. Like most of us.

849
00:58:45.530 --> 00:58:46.532
I'm sure.

850
00:58:48.576 --> 00:58:49.994
Um. do you know her name?

851
00:58:50.619 --> 00:58:55.083
It's Aidy or Ada.
something like that.

852
00:58:56.416 --> 00:58:59.295
Okay. Thank you.

853
00:59:00.380 --> 00:59:01.505
Look. I'm sorry
if I've ever...

854
00:59:01.588 --> 00:59:02.672
Can I go now?

855
00:59:05.135 --> 00:59:07.552
Yes. Thank you. sweetheart.

856
00:59:13.184 --> 00:59:14.434
I'm... I'm really sorry.
it's...

857
00:59:14.518 --> 00:59:16.228
No. no. no. it's... Honestly.

858
00:59:17.105 --> 00:59:18.313
You should see her fastball.

859
00:59:18.398 --> 00:59:21.400
I mean. she's just...

860
00:59:21.483 --> 00:59:23.693
...like. all day long.
I mean...

861
00:59:25.405 --> 00:59:27.364
Well. thanks. George.
I really have to...

862
00:59:28.239 --> 00:59:29.867
- Another time.
- Yeah.

863
00:59:29.951 --> 00:59:34.204
Uh. hey. maybe we can get a
drink together. huh? Sometime?

864
00:59:34.289 --> 00:59:36.916
Yeah. Yeah. that'd be great.

865
00:59:52.974 --> 00:59:54.434
I want to see <i>gege.</i>

866
00:59:56.561 --> 00:59:57.811
I know. love.

867
00:59:58.646 --> 01:00:03.150
You miss him. Me. too.
We just can't see him now.

868
01:00:05.735 --> 01:00:07.737
What about
the family dance?

869
01:00:08.364 --> 01:00:10.574
Are we never
gonna dance again?

870
01:00:10.657 --> 01:00:12.242
Of course we will.

871
01:00:13.452 --> 01:00:17.873
But we might have to compete
in the family of threes.

872
01:00:19.250 --> 01:00:21.918
I don't want
to be a family of three!

873
01:00:22.003 --> 01:00:23.003
Mika.

874
01:00:23.088 --> 01:00:25.047
I want <i>gege</i> back!

875
01:00:27.967 --> 01:00:30.469
Daddy's trying his best.
He's doing everything he can.

876
01:00:31.637 --> 01:00:32.847
I want him back. too.

877
01:00:36.476 --> 01:00:40.271
What about you. Mom?
Do you want him back?

878
01:00:42.606 --> 01:00:43.648
Of course I do.

879
01:00:53.076 --> 01:00:55.161
This is
dragging on too long.

880
01:00:57.204 --> 01:00:58.706
I just need
a little more time.

881
01:00:58.789 --> 01:01:01.708
Oh. we need
to start focusing on Mika.

882
01:01:02.335 --> 01:01:04.753
We're just making things
more difficult for her.

883
01:01:08.132 --> 01:01:12.012
Jake. do you hear me?

884
01:01:15.514 --> 01:01:17.474
If we can't get
Yang fixed. we just...

885
01:01:17.556 --> 01:01:19.978
we need to move forward. Okay?

886
01:01:20.061 --> 01:01:21.980
Now. Now.

887
01:01:23.398 --> 01:01:24.940
I need
to tell you something.

888
01:01:45.378 --> 01:01:46.628
<i>No. it's... it's frozen.</i>

889
01:01:46.710 --> 01:01:48.172
That's interesting.

890
01:01:48.255 --> 01:01:50.590
Try command
"memory reveal info."

891
01:01:50.675 --> 01:01:52.260
and it should tell you
if it's corrupt or not.

892
01:01:52.342 --> 01:01:53.344
Okay. I'll do that.

893
01:01:53.427 --> 01:01:55.679
Also. I was wondering.

894
01:01:55.762 --> 01:01:59.516
is it possible for
cultural technos like Yang to

895
01:02:00.726 --> 01:02:02.643
want to have
romantic potential?

896
01:02:03.103 --> 01:02:04.771
Do you mean
for humans to use them?

897
01:02:04.855 --> 01:02:08.900
No. no. no. I mean. for Yang
to be interested in...

898
01:02:08.985 --> 01:02:12.155
There's a girl. and she
showed up in his memories.

899
01:02:12.237 --> 01:02:14.907
and. you know. we didn't know
anything about her.

900
01:02:14.989 --> 01:02:16.117
Really?

901
01:02:16.909 --> 01:02:18.119
That's fascinating.

902
01:02:18.202 --> 01:02:20.329
because I've never
heard of cultural technos

903
01:02:20.413 --> 01:02:23.623
having that capacity.
I cannot tell you how much...

904
01:02:23.708 --> 01:02:25.210
...Yang and his memories...

905
01:02:25.585 --> 01:02:27.045
I should get that.

906
01:02:27.128 --> 01:02:29.588
Oh. all right. okay.
But we'll touch base soon?

907
01:02:29.672 --> 01:02:31.632
- Yeah. let's do that.
- Great.

908
01:02:37.637 --> 01:02:39.014
You've been
looking for me?

909
01:02:39.974 --> 01:02:41.184
Yes.

910
01:02:42.226 --> 01:02:43.478
I'm Jake.

911
01:02:44.518 --> 01:02:45.521
I know.

912
01:02:46.521 --> 01:02:47.606
I'm Ada.

913
01:02:48.315 --> 01:02:51.360
Ada. Well. come in. please.

914
01:02:52.445 --> 01:02:54.114
I knew something was wrong.

915
01:02:57.574 --> 01:03:00.244
We usually meet. and he wasn't
answering my messages.

916
01:03:04.123 --> 01:03:05.208
I'm sorry.

917
01:03:09.170 --> 01:03:10.295
I'm sorry.

918
01:03:12.297 --> 01:03:14.800
I know Yang loves
being a part of this family.

919
01:03:23.309 --> 01:03:24.643
Can I ask how you met?

920
01:03:26.686 --> 01:03:27.688
At the coffee shop.

921
01:03:29.773 --> 01:03:30.858
He approached you?

922
01:03:33.527 --> 01:03:35.487
He was a regular customer.

923
01:03:36.905 --> 01:03:39.034
He used to buy things
all the time. which.

924
01:03:39.117 --> 01:03:41.536
you know. was funny when
I found out he was a techno.

925
01:03:43.913 --> 01:03:45.581
But. yeah.
we started talking. and...

926
01:03:47.791 --> 01:03:50.210
eventually. he asked me
if I wanted to do something.

927
01:03:52.463 --> 01:03:53.672
Were you and Yang...

928
01:03:55.007 --> 01:03:56.217
Were you guys...

929
01:04:06.436 --> 01:04:08.813
Well. we never really
talked about us in that way.

930
01:04:25.829 --> 01:04:28.248
Sorry. that's...
That's my wife. I need to...

931
01:04:29.541 --> 01:04:30.543
- Yeah.
- Sorry.

932
01:04:30.626 --> 01:04:33.088
Please... don't leave.

933
01:04:38.175 --> 01:04:40.719
She's freaking out.
You need to pick her up.

934
01:04:40.802 --> 01:04:41.846
What's she doing?

935
01:04:41.929 --> 01:04:43.097
They said she punched a kid.

936
01:04:43.181 --> 01:04:44.764
and then she started
screaming at everyone.

937
01:04:44.849 --> 01:04:47.143
- Holy shit.
- Are you able to get her now?

938
01:04:47.559 --> 01:04:49.893
Yeah. Uh. yeah. I'm on my way.

939
01:04:49.980 --> 01:04:51.646
Thank you.

940
01:04:54.608 --> 01:04:56.235
I want to see him.

941
01:05:01.824 --> 01:05:02.951
Mika...

942
01:05:05.536 --> 01:05:07.246
Yang loves you so much.

943
01:05:08.539 --> 01:05:10.250
He always talks about you.

944
01:05:34.856 --> 01:05:36.858
- Thanks again for this.
- Oh. I understand.

945
01:05:36.942 --> 01:05:38.527
I'm sure everyone
misses him a lot.

946
01:05:42.572 --> 01:05:43.574
Mika.

947
01:05:50.123 --> 01:05:51.331
<i>Gege.</i>

948
01:05:55.795 --> 01:05:56.878
<i>Gege.</i>

949
01:05:58.088 --> 01:05:59.297
I'm sorry. baby.

950
01:06:00.675 --> 01:06:01.842
<i>Gege!</i>

951
01:06:50.056 --> 01:06:52.101
He would have his own area.

952
01:06:55.271 --> 01:07:00.985
We could put some
of his memories on a loop.

953
01:07:02.112 --> 01:07:03.487
projected.

954
01:07:04.239 --> 01:07:08.534
or on a set of readers
that visitors could wear.

955
01:07:16.583 --> 01:07:20.420
Of course. any memory would
have to be approved by you.

956
01:08:22.317 --> 01:08:23.399
Yang.

957
01:08:55.100 --> 01:08:56.100
Play.

958
01:09:24.462 --> 01:09:26.046
<i>Your collection
is growing.</i>

959
01:09:26.756 --> 01:09:28.381
Oh. hi.

960
01:09:29.134 --> 01:09:30.510
Yes. it's getting bigger.

961
01:09:31.801 --> 01:09:33.720
Do you want me to stop now?
I can put some away.

962
01:09:33.804 --> 01:09:36.015
No. no. I'm not complaining.

963
01:09:36.640 --> 01:09:38.725
I like them quite a bit.

964
01:09:39.269 --> 01:09:40.935
<i>Do you know
butterflies were one of</i>

965
01:09:41.020 --> 01:09:42.438
the favorite subjects
of Chinese trade art

966
01:09:42.520 --> 01:09:44.104
in the mid-1800s?

967
01:09:44.479 --> 01:09:46.109
No. I did not know that.

968
01:09:46.192 --> 01:09:48.528
The Chinese
love butterflies.

969
01:09:49.444 --> 01:09:51.572
There's also a famous
folk tale about two lovers

970
01:09:51.654 --> 01:09:54.533
who die of broken hearts
and reemerge as butterflies.

971
01:09:54.617 --> 01:09:58.162
Also. the ancient Chinese
philosopher Lao Tzu once said.

972
01:09:58.246 --> 01:10:00.456
"What the caterpillar
calls the end.

973
01:10:00.537 --> 01:10:03.082
"the rest of the world
calls a butterfly."

974
01:10:07.005 --> 01:10:08.006
I like that.

975
01:10:09.296 --> 01:10:11.634
I like that.

976
01:10:16.805 --> 01:10:18.224
Is this something you believe?

977
01:10:18.890 --> 01:10:21.310
- Hmm?
- That the end...

978
01:10:21.394 --> 01:10:24.479
That the end
is also a beginning?

979
01:10:24.564 --> 01:10:25.729
...is also

980
01:10:26.604 --> 01:10:27.733
the beginning?

981
01:10:31.487 --> 01:10:32.488
For the caterpillar...

982
01:10:32.572 --> 01:10:34.988
For the caterpillar. yes.

983
01:10:36.993 --> 01:10:39.453
But do you believe
it's true for all things?

984
01:10:42.912 --> 01:10:44.042
I don't know.

985
01:10:44.125 --> 01:10:47.962
I'm not programmed
to believe in that way.

986
01:10:48.046 --> 01:10:49.671
What about you?

987
01:10:54.469 --> 01:10:56.511
I'd like to believe that.

988
01:10:56.595 --> 01:10:58.555
Do you?

989
01:10:59.055 --> 01:11:00.140
Do you?

990
01:11:04.229 --> 01:11:05.645
Sometimes I think

991
01:11:07.273 --> 01:11:08.274
humans are programmed

992
01:11:08.358 --> 01:11:10.859
to believe
in such things. but...

993
01:11:14.904 --> 01:11:17.492
I don't know if it's really
in our best interest.

994
01:11:20.618 --> 01:11:22.578
May I be honest with you?

995
01:11:23.831 --> 01:11:26.126
Yes. Wait. is...

996
01:11:27.335 --> 01:11:29.252
Is not being honest
an option for you?

997
01:11:29.670 --> 01:11:31.296
I don't think so.

998
01:11:32.921 --> 01:11:35.385
Hmm.

999
01:11:38.554 --> 01:11:39.680
Go on.

1000
01:11:44.894 --> 01:11:50.439
I'm fine if there's
nothing in the end.

1001
01:11:55.029 --> 01:11:56.197
Are you?

1002
01:11:58.658 --> 01:12:01.077
Maybe I was programmed
this way as well.

1003
01:12:13.381 --> 01:12:15.341
Does it ever
make you feel sad?

1004
01:12:24.184 --> 01:12:25.185
Um...

1005
01:12:26.185 --> 01:12:29.604
There's no something
without nothing.

1006
01:12:40.613 --> 01:12:43.328
Does it ever
make you feel sad?

1007
01:12:44.118 --> 01:12:48.332
There's no something
without nothing.

1008
01:12:50.085 --> 01:12:51.127
Lao Tzu?

1009
01:12:52.670 --> 01:12:53.877
I'm not sure.

1010
01:13:17.653 --> 01:13:20.154
Did Yang ever struggle
with being a techno?

1011
01:13:25.118 --> 01:13:26.203
What do you mean?

1012
01:13:27.662 --> 01:13:31.832
I mean. did he ever...
want to be human?

1013
01:13:37.006 --> 01:13:38.131
What?

1014
01:13:40.010 --> 01:13:41.051
Nothing.

1015
01:13:45.265 --> 01:13:46.724
It's just...

1016
01:13:46.805 --> 01:13:49.144
That's such a human thing
to ask. isn't it?

1017
01:13:50.310 --> 01:13:51.729
We always assume
that other beings

1018
01:13:51.810 --> 01:13:52.854
would want to be human.

1019
01:13:52.938 --> 01:13:54.524
What's so great
about being human?

1020
01:13:55.649 --> 01:14:00.444
So he never struggled with it?
He never... Questioned it?

1021
01:14:04.283 --> 01:14:05.368
Not to me.

1022
01:14:08.703 --> 01:14:09.703
I see.

1023
01:14:17.837 --> 01:14:19.840
He did question
if he was Chinese.

1024
01:14:21.926 --> 01:14:22.926
He did?

1025
01:14:25.430 --> 01:14:26.430
Yeah.

1026
01:14:31.435 --> 01:14:34.020
What makes someone Asian?

1027
01:14:37.317 --> 01:14:38.774
He'd ask that all the time.

1028
01:14:41.319 --> 01:14:43.279
Maybe he just wanted
to help Mika understand

1029
01:14:43.363 --> 01:14:44.988
what it means to be Chinese.

1030
01:14:48.868 --> 01:14:51.122
He was dedicated
to his little sister.

1031
01:14:56.711 --> 01:14:58.337
Yeah. Yang was a good brother.

1032
01:15:01.506 --> 01:15:03.341
He's a great brother.

1033
01:16:51.701 --> 01:16:53.243
Reveal file info.

1034
01:16:53.786 --> 01:16:56.122
<i>Wrong command.
Try again.</i>

1035
01:16:57.457 --> 01:17:00.667
Reveal memory info.

1036
01:17:00.751 --> 01:17:03.796
<i>Access granted.
Beta archive.</i>

1037
01:17:03.877 --> 01:17:04.965
Beta archive.

1038
01:17:06.756 --> 01:17:07.756
Open.

1039
01:17:07.841 --> 01:17:10.261
<i>Wrong command. Try again.</i>

1040
01:17:10.345 --> 01:17:11.345
Extract.

1041
01:17:11.429 --> 01:17:12.511
<i>Full command.</i>

1042
01:17:13.180 --> 01:17:14.180
Extract beta.

1043
01:17:24.649 --> 01:17:25.818
Play all.

1044
01:17:52.551 --> 01:17:53.554
Zoom in.

1045
01:18:01.270 --> 01:18:02.313
Coordinates.

1046
01:18:07.943 --> 01:18:08.944
Hello.

1047
01:18:09.029 --> 01:18:11.072
Hi. uh.
could I speak to the owners?

1048
01:18:11.154 --> 01:18:12.657
Uh. yes. One moment.

1049
01:18:17.578 --> 01:18:19.997
<i>He wasn't just quiet.</i>

1050
01:18:20.081 --> 01:18:23.042
<i>He seemed despondent. Broken.</i>

1051
01:18:23.126 --> 01:18:24.792
We took him back
a few days later.

1052
01:18:24.877 --> 01:18:26.796
and they let us
make an exchange.

1053
01:18:26.877 --> 01:18:28.046
Brothers & Sisters?

1054
01:18:28.131 --> 01:18:29.840
No. it was. uh...

1055
01:18:32.010 --> 01:18:34.179
Well. I can't remember
the name.

1056
01:18:34.261 --> 01:18:35.761
We didn't buy him new.

1057
01:18:37.345 --> 01:18:38.349
You didn't?

1058
01:18:38.890 --> 01:18:40.810
No. but he was certified.

1059
01:18:41.894 --> 01:18:43.063
Second Siblings.

1060
01:18:43.895 --> 01:18:45.854
Maybe. Is that in Chinatown?

1061
01:18:45.939 --> 01:18:47.108
Yeah. it used to be.

1062
01:18:48.524 --> 01:18:52.113
I assume he was on when you
bought him in a sleep state?

1063
01:18:53.198 --> 01:18:54.282
That sounds right.

1064
01:19:00.997 --> 01:19:02.037
Extract

1065
01:19:03.916 --> 01:19:05.292
alpha.

1066
01:19:05.376 --> 01:19:07.212
<i>There is
not enough space.</i>

1067
01:19:07.295 --> 01:19:09.965
<i>Would you like to compress
beta or gamma?</i>

1068
01:19:10.631 --> 01:19:11.756
Compress beta.

1069
01:19:12.131 --> 01:19:13.426
<i>Beta compressed.</i>

1070
01:19:16.179 --> 01:19:17.470
Extract alpha.

1071
01:19:17.555 --> 01:19:19.599
<i>There is
not enough space.</i>

1072
01:19:19.680 --> 01:19:21.725
<i>Would you like
to compress gamma?</i>

1073
01:19:22.185 --> 01:19:23.435
Compress gamma.

1074
01:19:23.519 --> 01:19:25.145
<i>Gamma is compressing.</i>

1075
01:19:30.359 --> 01:19:31.569
<i>Gamma compressed.</i>

1076
01:19:43.912 --> 01:19:45.000
Extract alpha.

1077
01:20:12.359 --> 01:20:13.403
<i>Di-di.</i>

1078
01:20:28.082 --> 01:20:29.502
<i>Ni hao. di-di!</i>

1079
01:20:39.679 --> 01:20:41.095
<i>Di-di.</i> wake up.

1080
01:20:42.555 --> 01:20:43.849
<i>Di-di.</i>

1081
01:20:47.685 --> 01:20:49.604
<i>Is everything okay?</i>

1082
01:20:58.988 --> 01:21:00.283
We're going to miss you.

1083
01:21:25.555 --> 01:21:28.228
<i>Hi. we're here
to help Emma Davidson.</i>

1084
01:21:29.229 --> 01:21:30.854
<i>Yes. come in.</i>

1085
01:21:35.109 --> 01:21:36.859
Slowly bring it down.

1086
01:21:37.778 --> 01:21:39.072
Side to side.

1087
01:21:40.488 --> 01:21:41.573
Good.

1088
01:21:46.412 --> 01:21:48.662
Your niece
is going to like me.

1089
01:21:51.501 --> 01:21:54.502
Hey. Let's go get Yang.
Come here. Go get him.

1090
01:21:54.587 --> 01:21:56.587
You better not.

1091
01:22:04.095 --> 01:22:05.430
Can I tell you something?

1092
01:22:19.988 --> 01:22:21.072
Come on!

1093
01:23:30.390 --> 01:23:31.975
<i>She was my great aunt.</i>

1094
01:23:33.144 --> 01:23:34.145
<i>Your original?</i>

1095
01:23:35.438 --> 01:23:36.729
<i>So Yang knew her?</i>

1096
01:23:37.648 --> 01:23:38.649
<i>Yes.</i>

1097
01:23:40.024 --> 01:23:41.777
He never told you?

1098
01:23:45.073 --> 01:23:46.073
No.

1099
01:23:49.243 --> 01:23:51.537
But I always helped.

1100
01:23:56.876 --> 01:23:58.542
Sorry.

1101
01:24:11.724 --> 01:24:15.270
I wish he would have
told me about her. Us.

1102
01:24:16.479 --> 01:24:17.479
Do you?

1103
01:24:41.962 --> 01:24:43.046
He found you.

1104
01:25:48.863 --> 01:25:49.988
She's asleep.

1105
01:26:23.729 --> 01:26:27.609
I don't want Yang to be
on display in the museum.

1106
01:26:29.487 --> 01:26:30.569
Neither do I.

1107
01:26:31.822 --> 01:26:32.988
But...

1108
01:26:34.823 --> 01:26:36.702
We should let them study
his memories.

1109
01:26:40.122 --> 01:26:42.917
- Do you think so?
- Yes. his existence mattered.

1110
01:26:44.627 --> 01:26:45.795
And not just to us.

1111
01:26:52.635 --> 01:26:53.636
Yeah.

1112
01:28:32.734 --> 01:28:33.944
<i>Gege.</i>

1113
01:29:00.636 --> 01:29:01.639
Daddy.

1114
01:29:02.640 --> 01:29:04.100
Hey. what are you doing up?

1115
01:29:05.143 --> 01:29:06.475
What are you doing?

1116
01:29:08.729 --> 01:29:09.729
You want some water?

1117
01:29:11.899 --> 01:29:13.109
Want to sit beside me?

1118
01:29:25.371 --> 01:29:26.537
Can't sleep.

1119
01:29:27.957 --> 01:29:28.957
Me neither.

1120
01:29:31.417 --> 01:29:33.377
Don't want to say bye to <i>gege.</i>

1121
01:29:34.837 --> 01:29:35.840
Me neither.

1122
01:29:42.011 --> 01:29:45.265
<i>I want to be</i>

1123
01:29:48.228 --> 01:29:51.439
<i>I want to be</i>

1124
01:29:53.689 --> 01:29:58.529
<i>I want to be
just like a melody</i>

1125
01:29:59.279 --> 01:30:02.823
<i>Just like a simple sound</i>

1126
01:30:02.908 --> 01:30:06.037
<i>Like a harmony</i>
